01/04/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic met on Monday (March 31st) with the ambassadors of NATO member countries in Podgorica. He said they agreed that Montenegro has proved itself a credible partner of the international community and has met the preconditions for accession to both NATO and the EU. After meeting, Djukanovic reiterated Montenegro's plans to continue its intensive efforts to integrate into Euro-Atlantic structures. Opportunities for countries in the Western Balkans will be a key topic of the NATO summit which opens in Bucharest on Wednesday. (Vijesti - 01/04/08; RTCG - 31/03/08)
